(firstQuint)Cervical Recuperation After Vaginal Delivery.

 Patients after vaginal delivery will be recruited after receiving a full explanation and signing an informed consent.

 The goal of the study is to examine cervical length after vaginal delivery at 3 different time intervals: 1.

 8 hours post delivery.

 2.

 24 hours post delivery.

 3.

 48 hours post delivery.

 At each interval a trans-vaginal ultrasound will be performed, evaluating cervical length.

 At the end of the 3rd and final ultrasound, the patient will finish her participation in the study/ Information regarding obstetric conditions such as labor induction, gestational age at the time of delivery etc.

 will be collected from patients` electronic files.

